# SDK Forge — Cursor Agent Rules

## Project

- **Name:** SDK Forge (`sdk-forge` pip package, `forge` CLI)
- **Repo:** https://github.com/weininghui/TestAgent (may rename to `sdk-forge`)
- **Python:** 3.10+; layered package under `sdk_forge/`

## Layered imports (v5.11+)

Root `sdk_forge/` keeps only `cli.py`, `__init__.py`, `__main__.py`. **No flat shims.**

| Area | Module prefix |
|------|----------------|
| Scan / build / enrich | `sdk_forge.pipeline.*` |
| Orchestration | `sdk_forge.orchestration.*` |
| Delegation / task dispatch | `sdk_forge.delegation.*` |
| Config / gtest / doctor | `sdk_forge.infra.*` |
| Domain models / util | `sdk_forge.domain.*` |

MCP tools live in `mcp_server.py`; add tests in `tests/test_mcp_server.py`.

See [docs/MIGRATION_v5.11.md](docs/MIGRATION_v5.11.md) for full import table.

## Code style

- Follow [docs/CONVENTIONS.md](docs/CONVENTIONS.md): bilingual docstrings (EN + CN) for public APIs
- MCP tool `description` fields: English
- Default **中文** when replying to the user; keep commands/paths in English
- Minimize scope; match existing patterns; no over-engineering

## Tests

```bash
# Fast (no C++ build)
python -m pytest tests/ -v -k "not TestCompileAndRun and not TestCoveragePipeline and not TestCliIntegration"

# Windows integration subset (before release)
python -m pytest tests/ -v -k "TestCompileAndRun and not pkg_config and not test_medium"
python -m pytest tests/ -v -k TestCliIntegration
```

## Release files (must stay in sync)

When bumping version, update all of:

- `sdk_forge/__init__.py` → `__version__`
- `pyproject.toml` → `version`
- `plugin.yaml` → `version`
- `CHANGELOG.md`
- `docs/releases/RELEASE_NOTES_vX.Y.Z.md`
- `README.md` / `README.zh-CN.md` (current release link)
- `docs/INSTALL.md` / `docs/INSTALL.zh-CN.md` (current release + verify examples)

Use `scripts/release.ps1 -Version X.Y.Z` when available.

Process: [docs/RELEASE_PROCESS.md](docs/RELEASE_PROCESS.md)

## OpenCode sync

After release: `scripts/update-opencode-plugin.ps1 -Ref vX.Y.Z` then restart OpenCode.

## Git safety

- **Only commit/push when the user explicitly asks**
- Never force-push to `main`
- Never commit secrets (`model_config.local.yaml`, `.forge/`, credentials)

## Agent docs sync

When changing forge orchestration or MCP tools, also update:

- `.opencode/agents/forge.md`
- `.opencode/skills/sdk-forge/SKILL.md`
- `docs/AGENTS.md`
